  "text": "MIT just tested 30 AI agents on real-world tasks. Not toy benchmarks. Real tasks. Filing taxes, booking flights, managing spreadsheets. Every single one failed. The best agent completed just 43% of tasks. The worst? Under 10%. And here's the scary part. These are the agents companies are selling you right now. The ones claiming to replace your entire workforce. MIT found they break on simple things Pop-up windows Changed layouts, multi-step forms The kind of stuff a human handles without thinking AI agents aren't ready Not even close So the next time someone tries to sell you a fully autonomous AI worker Show them this study Follow for more AI reality checks"
